{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 204 "5.  Three-dimensional pl
ots.  Maple can also provide representations for graphs of functions o
f two variables.  The graphs of such functions are surfaces in three-d
imensional space.  The Maple command is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " }{TEXT 270 0 "" }{TEXT 271 
4 "plot" }{TEXT 272 2 "3d" }{TEXT -1 2 "( " }{TEXT 273 4 "expr" }
{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 274 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 8 "=range, " }{TEXT 275 0 "
" }{TEXT 276 2 "y=" }{TEXT -1 19 "range [, options]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 277 4 "e
xpr" }{TEXT 281 1 " " }{TEXT -1 24 "is a symbolic expression" }{TEXT 
279 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "which represents the function to be plotted an
d " }{TEXT 278 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 282 0 "" }{TEXT 283 1 
"y" }{TEXT 284 0 "" }{TEXT -1 44 " are the two independent variables u
sed in  " }{TEXT 280 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 25 "  to define the function.
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " 
}{TEXT 285 0 "" }{TEXT 286 6 "plot3d" }{TEXT 287 0 "" }{TEXT -1 238 " \+
command will generate a surface plot for the function over the rectang
ular range specfied in the command statement.  The surface plot can be
 rotated, tipped over and turned around to see the surface plot from a
ll side and all viewpoints." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 278 "For each of the following functions provide a \+
plot which shows the graph.  Choose reasonable values for the ranges o
f x and y.  Rotate, where appropriate, to present a good view of the g
raph.  The last two graphs are implicitly defined functions which requ
ire the Maple command " }{TEXT 297 0 "" }{TEXT 298 15 "implicitplot3d \+
" }{TEXT 299 0 "" }{TEXT -1 29 "which is part of the package " }{TEXT 
300 0 "" }{TEXT 301 5 "plots" }{TEXT 302 0 "" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "a.   " }
